" You need focus , and experience . "
Indeed , to pick tea you have to take into account the weather and then , after selecting just the right time to pick , you carry out a series of fermentation steps that vary depending on just what the leaves are like that day .
How long should the leaves ferment outdoors ?
How long indoors ?
These questions are decided by <COREF ID="2" TYPE="IDENT">the grower</COREF> , using everything at <COREF ID="2" TYPE="IDENT">his</COREF> disposal - eyes , nose , heart , mind , mouth , and hands , all working in harmony .
A tiny bit more , a second less - it 's a discipline and an art .
Following fermentation , step by step , <COREF ID="14" TYPE="IDENT">the tips</COREF> are withered and crumbled , any lumps are broken up , then <COREF ID="14" TYPE="IDENT">the tips</COREF> are fired .
Each of these steps affects the quality of the finished product .
The timing must be accurately calculated , the temperature must be precise .
Unfortunately , there are no standards to follow .
Absolutely everything relies on each grower 's store of personal experience .
