<COREF ID="31" TYPE="IDENT">The township chief</COREF> throws up <COREF ID="31" TYPE="IDENT">his</COREF> hands and comments with exasperation that in everything <COREF ID="18" TYPE="IDENT">the government</COREF> has done <COREF ID="18" TYPE="IDENT">it</COREF> has treated <COREF ID="6" TYPE="IDENT">the local people</COREF> officiously and shown no confidence in <COREF ID="6" TYPE="IDENT">them</COREF> .
In <COREF ID="31" TYPE="IDENT">his</COREF> view , <COREF ID="18" TYPE="IDENT">the government</COREF> should think of some way whereby both <COREF ID="20" TYPE="IDENT">Pinglin</COREF> and the water resource protection zone can coexist and prosper .
